  "prompt": "What happens when you withdraw linkedin invitation?",
  "response": "When you withdraw a LinkedIn invitation, several things occur:\n\n1. **Cancellation of Invitation:** The invitation that you originally sent is canceled immediately. This means the recipient will no longer have the option to accept or decline your connection request.\n\n2. **Notification:** The recipient will not be notified that you have withdrawn the invitation. LinkedIn does not send alerts or messages about withdrawn invitations.\n\n3. **Re-sending Option:** You can send another connection request to the same person if you choose to do so. However, you may need to wait a certain period, often up to 3 weeks, before LinkedIn allows you to resend an invitation to the same person.\n\n4. **List Update:** The withdrawn invitation will also be removed from the list of pending invitations in your LinkedIn \"My Network\" section, allowing you to better manage your remaining pending requests.\n\nOverall, withdrawing an invitation on LinkedIn simply retracts the connection request with no further notifications or implications for either party.",
